title: 820-00165-A
message:
Hi, 820-00165-A board with no visible corrosion. Green and orange light, no fan spin. Trying to turn on SMC bypass no fan spin. 

no  PP5V_S4RS3  and no  PP5V_S0. 

5 volts on  PP5V_S5 .

P5VS0_EN is not present.

title: 820-00165-A
message:
Do you get 3V3_S5/SUS?
What about SMC_ADAPTER_EN, PM_BATLOW_L, PM_DSW_PWRGD, PCH_DSWVRMEN, PM_RSMRST_L and PM_PWRBTN_L?

title: 820-00165-A
message: PCH_DSWVRMEN is 3.3v steady. Rest is not present.

title: 820-00165-A
message:
Exact PPBUS_G3H voltage (without battery)?
SMC_RESET_L present?
Also check DC voltage at Y5110 (if no o-scope available).

title: 820-00165-A
message:
PPBUS_G3H is 8.56v

SMC_RESET_L: 3.38v

SMC_EXTAL:0.9 v

SMC_XTAL_R: 0v

title: 820-00165-A
message:
Last value looks strange, but SMC works; as you get correct PPBUS_G3H.

"Do you get 3V3_S5/SUS?"
???

title: 820-00165-A
message:
Really strange to get 5V_S5, but no 3V3_S5.
Check diode mode to ground at L7560 first.
Post basic voltage for U7501; pins 23, 22, 12, 13, 29, 21.

title: 820-00165-A
message: 3V3_S5 should then be present at L7560; check it again.

title: 820-00165-A
message: I still get 0v both on P3V3_S5_REG_L and P3V3_S5_REG_R.

title: 820-00165-A
message:
Check all U7501 surrounded components, related to 3V3_S5 section.
Pay atention to R/C7564.
May need to change U7501 and Q7560.

title: 820-00165-A
message: Yeah, just finished replacing U7501 and fans spinning. lets see if it boots.
